Jenkins master :-
 ADD password to jenkins
 # sudo passwd jenkins

If you want to use vi or vim instead of nano as your default editor for visudo, you can run:
#sudo EDITOR=vim visudo
insidefile changes 
#jenkins ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL

permisson BIN
#vim /etc/passwd
---> bin/bash

authentication SSHD
#vim /etc/ssh/sshd_config
-->passwd authentication yes

Jenkins slave :-
ADD user/ password to jenkins
#useradd jenkins
# sudo passwd jenkins
If you want to use vi or vim instead of nano as your default editor for visudo, you can run:
#sudo EDITOR=vim visudo
insidefile changes 
#jenkins ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL

authentication SSHD
#vim /etc/ssh/sshd_config
-->passwd authentication yes




